The paper deals with the computational complexity of the Rainbow k-Coloring problem, which is a graph coloring problem. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to graph theory and algorithms. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category since the paper deals with the algorithmic complexity of a graph coloring problem. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely category since the paper provides lower bounds on the running time of algorithms for the Rainbow k-Coloring problem. 

cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category since the paper deals with graph coloring, which is a fundamental problem in game theory. 

cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category since the paper deals with graph coloring, which is a problem that arises in computational geometry. 

cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category since the paper deals with graph coloring, which is a topic in discrete mathematics.
